  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators believe that the local anesthetic EMLA (Lidocaine 2.5% and Prilocaine 2.5%)
      cream will lessen pain and reduce the need for anesthesia and analgesia, when implanting a
      permanent pacemaker.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
